headline: Medtronic advances its innovation strategy with intent to acquire CathWorks
summary: Medtronic plc (NYSE:MDT), a global leader in healthcare technology, today announced it will exercise its option to acquire CathWorks, a privately held medical device company, which aims to transform how coronary artery disease (CAD) is diagnosed and treated. The intent to acquire CathWorks follows a 2022 strategic partnership with a co-promotion agreement for the CathWorks FFRangio® System in the U.S., Europe and Japan, where it is commercially available. The acquisition is valued at up to $585
